WEBVTT

00:02.470 --> 00:04.272
HMM.

00:04.305 --> 00:06.807
CHECK OUT THIS LETTER
TO THE EDITOR.

00:06.840 --> 00:09.110
APPARENTLY,
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY GUY

00:09.143 --> 00:11.479
WHO THINKS BIG MEDIA
AND BIG BUSINESS

00:11.512 --> 00:14.115
ARE CRUSHING THE HUMANITY
OUT OF HUMANITY.

00:14.148 --> 00:15.649
I'M GONNA CRUSH THE HUMANITY
OUT OF YOU

00:15.683 --> 00:17.318
IF YOUNO, SERIOUSLY.LKING.

00:17.351 --> 00:18.986
SOUNDS LIKE YOU
ON ONE OF YOUR RANTS.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.921
LISTEN TO THIS.

00:20.954 --> 00:23.524
"WHEN YOU DEVOTE
NOT EVEN A SINGLE PAGE

00:23.557 --> 00:26.560
"TO ANYTHING OTHER
THAN YOUR SLAVISHLY FAWNING

00:26.594 --> 00:27.828
"SO-CALLED 'NEWS,'

00:27.861 --> 00:30.664
"PANDERING TO CORPORATE
ADVERTISERS,

00:30.698 --> 00:31.999
"YOU DESTROY ALL HOPE
OF TOMORROW

00:32.032 --> 00:35.369
FOR HONEST,
HARDWORKING AMERICANS."

00:36.870 --> 00:39.006
"WOW!
HOW INTRIGUING, MAX.

00:39.039 --> 00:40.674
"THANK YOU
FOR SHARING SOMETHING

00:40.708 --> 00:42.143
"YOU THOUGHT
WOULD INTEREST ME.

00:42.176 --> 00:44.178
"OH, AND THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR THE PAPAYA.

00:44.212 --> 00:46.314
IT'S DELICIOUS."

00:46.347 --> 00:47.481
ACTUALLY,
IT COULD USE A LITTLE LIME.

00:49.250 --> 00:52.019
YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:52.052 --> 00:53.521
GET IT YOURSELF.

00:53.554 --> 00:54.522
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

00:54.555 --> 00:55.589
YOU HEARD ME.

00:55.623 --> 00:57.057
AND AS OF RIGHT NOW,

00:57.091 --> 00:59.860
YOUR ASSISTANT
IS OFFICIALLY ON STRIKE.

00:59.893 --> 01:03.364
IF THIS IS ABOUT A RAISE,
YOU MIGHT WANT TO CONSIDER

01:03.397 --> 01:05.533
A SLIGHTLY LESS
MELODRAMATIC APPROACH.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.368
IT'S NOT ABOUT
THE MONEY, DOC.

01:07.401 --> 01:09.337
IT'S ABOUT
THE WORKING CONDITIONS.

01:09.370 --> 01:12.540
OKAY, IT'S ABOUT YOU SHOWING ME
A LITTLE COMMON COURTESY.

01:12.573 --> 01:15.543
WHAT ARE YOU -- LEWICKI!

01:15.576 --> 01:19.113
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
I'LL READ THE [BLEEP] LETTER.

01:19.147 --> 01:22.150
[ SIGHS ]

01:24.585 --> 01:28.389
[ TAPPING ]

01:33.927 --> 01:35.396
WHO ARE YOU?

01:35.429 --> 01:37.231
[ British accent ]
OH, UH, I'M AFRAID

01:37.265 --> 01:40.401
MY IDENTITY IS CLASSIFIED,
OLD BOY.

01:40.434 --> 01:42.770
YOU'RE A HALLUCINATION.

01:44.104 --> 01:45.573
WHOSE ASSISTANCE
YOU'LL REQUIRE

01:45.606 --> 01:47.541
IF YOU HAVE ANY HOPE
OF CRACKING THAT CODE.

01:49.543 --> 01:50.544
WHAT CODE?

01:50.578 --> 01:51.945
COME NOW, OLD BOY.

01:53.147 --> 01:56.250
SURELY YOU NOTICED
THE AWKWARD SYNTAX.

01:56.284 --> 02:01.555
"SLAVISHLY FAWNING
SO-CALLED NEWS"?

02:01.589 --> 02:03.757
CLEARLY THE WORDS
HAVE BEEN TWISTED

02:03.791 --> 02:05.926
AROUND SOME SORT OF
HIDDEN MESSAGE.

02:05.959 --> 02:08.196
THERE'S MY BOY.

02:09.630 --> 02:11.665
Daniel:
IT'S STEGANOGRAPHY.

02:11.699 --> 02:13.934
HIDDEN WRITING.
LOOK.

02:13.967 --> 02:16.604
IF YOU READ EVERY 10th WORD,
LOOK WHAT YOU GET.

02:17.771 --> 02:19.740
"YOU'LL BE PROUD OF ME.

02:19.773 --> 02:24.612
"FRONT-PAGE NEWS TOMORROW.
ONE DOWN, FOUR TO GO.

02:24.645 --> 02:27.047
THE BUTCHER TOLD ME
WHERE TO START."

02:27.080 --> 02:28.649
IT'S HOW THE FRENCH
RESISTANCE COMMUNICATED

02:28.682 --> 02:30.451
WITH BRITISH INTELLIGENCE
DURING WORLD WAR II --

02:30.484 --> 02:31.685
WITH MESSAGES
IN THE NEWSPAPER,

02:31.719 --> 02:32.953
RIGHT WHERE ANYBODY
COULD SEE.

02:32.986 --> 02:34.888
FRENCH RESISTANCE?

02:34.922 --> 02:36.290
WOW.

02:36.324 --> 02:38.125
MEANWHILE,
BACK ON THE PLANE OF REALITY,

02:38.158 --> 02:39.593
SOME OF US
HAVE WORK TO DO.

02:39.627 --> 02:41.795
THINK ABOUT IT, KATE.

02:41.829 --> 02:43.130
WHAT ENDS UP
ON THE FRONT PAGE?

02:43.163 --> 02:45.633
WORLD NOR CRIME.TICS...

02:45.666 --> 02:47.301
I'M GUESSING
WHOEVER WROTE THIS

02:47.335 --> 02:49.270
IS SENDING A MESSAGE
TO AN ACCOMPLICE.

02:49.303 --> 02:50.671
"ONE DOWN, FOUR TO GO" --

02:50.704 --> 02:52.906
THAT COULD BE BANKS TO ROB
OR VICTIMS TO BUTCHER.

02:52.940 --> 02:55.909
DO YOU THINK
THAT THIS MIGHT BE YOU...

02:55.943 --> 03:00.080
MAKING CONNECTIONS WHERE
POSSIBLY THERE AREN'T ANY?

03:00.113 --> 03:02.149
WHAT ARE THE CHANCES
OF EVERY 10th WORD

03:02.182 --> 03:04.818
IN SOME RANDOM PIECE OF TEXT
MAKING THIS MUCH SENSE?

03:04.852 --> 03:06.620
OR IT COULD BE SOMETHING
COMPLETELY INNOCENT.

03:06.654 --> 03:08.789
THEN WHY HIDE IT
IN A CODE?

03:08.822 --> 03:11.091
LOOK AT THE GUY'S NAME --
JAMES SMITH.

03:11.124 --> 03:13.193
IT'S GOT TO BE THE MOST COMMON
NAME IN AMERICA.

03:13.227 --> 03:14.862
IT'S OBVIOUSLY AN ALIAS.

03:14.895 --> 03:16.964
AND WHY USE AN ALIAS UNLESS
YOU'RE DOING SOMETHING ILLICIT?

03:16.997 --> 03:19.933
ALL RIGHT, LOOK, THE LETTER
PROBABLY CAME IN VIA E-MAIL.

03:19.967 --> 03:22.002
THERE MIGHT BE SOME WAY
TO TRACE THE I.P.,

03:22.035 --> 03:24.505
BUT IT COULD BE FROM
AN INTERNET CAFÃ© IN SINGAPORE.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.474
Probert: YOU'RE ACTUALLY
TAKING THIS SERIOUSLY?

03:26.507 --> 03:28.509
I WANT TO BE THERE
WHEN YOU TELL THE BOSS

03:28.542 --> 03:30.177
THAT WE'RE TAKING ON A CASE

03:30.210 --> 03:32.313
THAT DR. STRANGE FOUND
WITH HIS SECRET DECODER RING.

03:32.346 --> 03:33.347
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

03:33.381 --> 03:37.351
MORETTI.

03:37.385 --> 03:38.686
WHAT?

03:38.719 --> 03:40.120
OKAY,
WE'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

03:40.153 --> 03:42.356
THAT WAS THE CPD.

03:42.390 --> 03:43.757
THEY NEED OUR HELP WITH
A POSSIBLE TERRORIST ATTACK.

03:43.791 --> 03:46.460
A LAWYER DOWNTOWN
OPENED UP A PACKAGE

03:46.494 --> 03:48.128
AND GOT SPRAYED IN THE FACE
WITH SARIN.

03:48.161 --> 03:50.130
DIED BEFORE PARAMEDICS
GOT THERE.

03:50.163 --> 03:51.532
OF COURSE, A LAWYER,

03:51.565 --> 03:54.835
BECAUSE THE BUTCHER TOLD HIM
WHERE TO START.

03:54.868 --> 03:56.670
WHAT THE [BLEEP]
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

03:56.704 --> 03:58.171
IT'S SHAKESPEARE --
"HENRY VI, PART 2."

03:58.205 --> 03:59.873
DICK THE BUTCHER SAYS,
"FIRST THING WE DO,

03:59.907 --> 04:01.375
LET'S KILL
ALL THE LAWYERS."

04:01.409 --> 04:02.776
A SARIN ATTACK.

04:02.810 --> 04:06.179
THAT SOUNDS LIKE
FRONT-PAGE NEWS TO ME.

04:15.323 --> 04:17.791
Maya: [ Voice breaking ]
NORMALLY, I OPEN

04:17.825 --> 04:19.993
MR. SCANTLIN'S MAIL
MYSELF,

04:20.027 --> 04:22.796
BUT THERE WAS A BOX
MARKED "PERSONAL."

04:22.830 --> 04:24.798
HE THOUGHT SOMEONE
SENT HIM A PRESENT,

04:24.832 --> 04:27.000
SO HE OPENED IT HIMSELF.

04:27.034 --> 04:30.404
AND THERE WAS A POP,
LIKE A FIRECRACKER,

04:30.438 --> 04:33.273
AND SOME KIND OF SPRAY
CAME OUT.

04:33.307 --> 04:35.075
AND HE STARTED TWITCHING.

04:35.108 --> 04:36.677
I TRIED TO HELP HIM.

04:36.710 --> 04:39.112
THERE'S NOTHING YOU COULD
HAVE DONE, MISS BENOWITZ.

04:39.146 --> 04:40.814
SARIN IS MORE TOXIC
THAN CYANIDE.

04:40.848 --> 04:43.250
Kate:
CAN YOU THINK OF ANYBODY

04:43.283 --> 04:45.619
WHO MIGHT HAVE HAD A REASON
TO DO THIS?

04:45.653 --> 04:48.956
TOM WAS A MENSCH.
EVERYBODY LOVED HIM.

04:48.989 --> 04:52.593
BUT HE WAS A TRIAL LAWYER.
HE WON A LOT OF CASES.

04:52.626 --> 04:55.929
I MEAN, THE --
THE LOSERS WEREN'T HAPPY.

04:55.963 --> 04:58.599
THERE IS NOTHING
ON THE PACKAGE --

04:58.632 --> 05:00.200
NO PRINTS,
NO RETURN ADDRESS.

05:00.233 --> 05:02.770
ALL RIGHT, WELL, WE'LL TALK
TO HIS FRIENDS, RELATIVES,

05:02.803 --> 05:04.271
ACQUAINTANCES,

05:04.304 --> 05:06.273
BUT I THINK WE SHOULD START
WITH HIS CASE FILES.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.609
FARRINGTON
v. AWAKAMA SUSHI.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.110
SCANTLIN GOT AWAKAMA
FOR 7 MIL

05:10.143 --> 05:12.045
FOR A SINGLE CASE
OF E. COLI.

05:12.079 --> 05:13.280
HERE'S SOMETHING.

05:13.313 --> 05:15.048
MILLER v. KLAUSNER
EXTERMINATION.

05:15.082 --> 05:17.485
KLAUSNER WAS ORDERED TO PAY
$70,000 IN MEDICAL EXPENSES,

05:17.518 --> 05:19.653
$1.4 MILLION PUNITIVE.

05:19.687 --> 05:20.854
THIS COULD BE OUR GUY.

05:20.888 --> 05:23.056
WHY HIM
OUT OF ALL THESE CASES?

05:23.090 --> 05:24.625
SARIN'S A NERVE AGENT,

05:24.658 --> 05:26.494
BUT IT WAS ORIGINALLY DEVELOPED
AS A PESTICIDE.

05:26.527 --> 05:28.496
AN EXTERMINATOR WOULD HAVE
EVERYTHING HE NEEDED

05:28.529 --> 05:30.330
TO MIX UP A BATCH,
RIGHT ON THE SHELF.

05:31.499 --> 05:34.134
Klausner: YEAH.
I HATE TOM SCANTLIN.

05:34.167 --> 05:36.470
I BUILT MY BUSINESS
FROM NOTHING.

05:36.504 --> 05:39.473
32 TRUCKS, 58 EMPLOYEES,

05:39.507 --> 05:41.675
CONTRACTS WITH EVERY SCHOOL
DISTRICT IN THE COUNTY.

05:41.709 --> 05:44.812
NOT BAD FOR A GUY WHO NEVER
GOT PAST EIGHTH GRADE, HUH?

05:44.845 --> 05:46.814
AND THAT S.O.B.
TOOK IT ALL AWAY.

05:46.847 --> 05:48.482
ACTUALLY,
IT WAS A JURY OF YOUR PEERS

05:48.516 --> 05:50.484
WHO DECIDED AGAINST YOU.

05:50.518 --> 05:52.085
THEY DECIDED WRONG.

05:52.119 --> 05:54.488
LBJ ELEMENTARY HAD ROACHES
THE SIZE OF CHIPMUNKS.

05:54.522 --> 05:56.089
SO MY GUYS SPRAYED
WITH A VERY RELIABLE PESTICIDE

05:56.123 --> 05:58.492
I IMPORTED FROM MEXICO.

05:58.526 --> 05:59.960
WHICH YOU HAD TO DO

05:59.993 --> 06:01.995
BECAUSE IT WASN'T YET APPROVED
HERE IN THE U.S.

06:02.029 --> 06:04.297
THEY USE THAT STUFF LIKE KETCHUP
ON FRIES SOUTH OF THE BORDER,

06:04.331 --> 06:05.699
AND NO ONE'S COMPLAINING.

06:05.733 --> 06:08.101
SOMEONE NORTH OF THE BORDER
SURE COMPLAINED.

06:08.135 --> 06:09.537
ONE KID CRIES SICK,

06:09.570 --> 06:10.838
AND HIS PARENTS
GET A FAST-TALKING LAWYER

06:10.871 --> 06:12.205
WHO SUES THE CRAP
OUT OF ME.

06:13.441 --> 06:15.208
ON THE NEWS,
HE MADE IT SOUND

06:15.242 --> 06:17.144
LIKE I DELIBERATELY SET OUT
TO POISON SCHOOLCHILDREN.

06:20.814 --> 06:24.351
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY THAT
YOU SHOULD MENTION THE NEWS,

06:24.384 --> 06:26.186
BECAUSE THERE WAS
A LETTER TO THE EDITOR

06:26.219 --> 06:27.821
IN TODAY'S PAPER

06:27.855 --> 06:30.624
ABOUT HOW THE MEDIA IS STACKED
AGAINST THE LITTLE GUY.

06:30.658 --> 06:32.292
YOU MIGHT
FIND IT INTERESTING.

06:32.325 --> 06:35.195
GO AHEAD. READ IT.

06:35.228 --> 06:37.698
SORRY, I DON'T HAVE
MY READING GLASSES.

06:37.731 --> 06:39.700
MAYBE YOU DON'T NEED
TO READ IT

06:39.733 --> 06:40.734
BECAUSE YOU ALREADY KNOW WHAT
IT SAYS BECAUSE YOU WROTE IT.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.002
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

06:42.035 --> 06:43.637
I DON'T WRITE LETTERS
TO THE PAPERS.

06:43.671 --> 06:44.905
LISTEN, JUST BECAUSE
I HATED SCANTLIN

06:44.938 --> 06:46.306
DOESN'T MEAN
THAT I KILLED HIM.

06:46.339 --> 06:48.075
SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

06:48.108 --> 06:51.479
I JUST -- I WANTED TO OFFER
MR. KLAUSNER MY READING GLASSES.

06:54.247 --> 06:58.085
YEAH, UH, I PROBABLY GOT
A DIFFERENT PRESCRIPTION.

06:58.118 --> 07:00.087
ALL RIGHT. I THINK
I UNDERSTAND WHAT'S GOING ON.

07:00.120 --> 07:03.056
DO -- DO YOU HAVE DYSLEXIA,
MR. KLAUSNER?

07:03.090 --> 07:04.458
HOW DID YOU --

07:04.492 --> 07:06.894
IT WOULD HELP EXPLAIN
WHY A MAN AS SMART AS YOU

07:06.927 --> 07:08.261
DIDN'T MAKE IT
PAST EIGHTH GRADE,

07:08.295 --> 07:09.396
AND WHY YOU DON'T
WANT TO READ THE LETTER.

07:09.429 --> 07:11.465
IT'S NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

07:11.499 --> 07:12.700
IT JUST MEANS
YOU'RE NOT OUR MAN.

07:12.733 --> 07:13.967
Probert:
JUST BECAUSE HE'S DYSLEXIC

07:14.001 --> 07:15.603
DOESN'T MEAN HE'S INNOCENT.

07:15.636 --> 07:18.672
PROBERT, FOR HIM, WORDS AND
LETTERS SWIM AROUND THE PAGE.

07:18.706 --> 07:21.441
SO, SADLY, HE AVOIDS READING
AND WRITING ALTOGETHER.

07:21.475 --> 07:23.711
IT'S NOT LIKE HE SUDDENLY
WOKE UP ONE MORNING

07:23.744 --> 07:25.479
AND DECIDED TO START
COMMUNICATING

07:25.513 --> 07:27.180
BY CONSTRUCTING
ELABORATE CODES

07:27.214 --> 07:29.049
BURIED INSIDE
LETTERS TO THE EDITOR.

07:29.082 --> 07:32.052
SO IT'S BACK TO THE
NEEDLE-IN-A-HAYSTACK STRATEGY.

07:32.085 --> 07:34.387
ACTUALLY,
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

07:34.421 --> 07:38.091
THERE MAY BE A WAY TO GET
THE NEEDLE TO COME TO US.

07:38.125 --> 07:42.295
IN HIS CODE, THE KILLER SAYS,
"YOU'LL BE PROUD OF ME."

07:42.329 --> 07:44.865
HE'S LOOKING
FOR APPROVAL.

07:44.898 --> 07:46.299
IF I WRITE HIM BACK,

07:46.333 --> 07:47.768
TELL HIM WHAT A GREAT JOB
I THINK HE'S DOING,

07:47.801 --> 07:49.269
MAYBE HE'LL TALK TO ME.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.605
YOU PLAN ON MAKING FRIENDS
WITH THIS LUNATIC?

07:51.639 --> 07:54.775
WE'RE PEAS IN A POD.

07:54.808 --> 07:56.744
Kate:
"YOU THINK YOU HAVE GUTS,

07:56.777 --> 07:58.812
BUT ALL I HEAR IS WHINING
AND SELF-PITY."

07:58.846 --> 08:00.080
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING TO DO,

08:00.113 --> 08:01.582
GET HIM TO SARIN-GAS
THE WHOLE CITY?

08:01.615 --> 08:03.216
I THOUGHT THIS WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE A FAN LETTER.

08:03.250 --> 08:04.952
HAVE YOU CONSIDERED REQUESTING
A NEW PARTNER?

08:04.985 --> 08:07.621
YOU'RE JUST TRYING TO GET
HIS ATTEXACTLY.RIGHT?

08:07.655 --> 08:09.122
IF HE'S AS SMART
AS I THINK HE IS,

08:09.156 --> 08:10.390
HE'LL SEE
THE HIDDEN MESSAGE.

08:10.423 --> 08:11.759
EVERY 10 WORDS,
YOU SAID?

08:14.928 --> 08:16.463
Daniel: "GREAT MOVE.

08:16.496 --> 08:20.634
"I WISH I HAD YOUR GUTS.

08:20.668 --> 08:24.304
"JUST ONE QUESTION --

08:24.337 --> 08:28.976
"OUT OF ALL THE LYING, CHEATING
LAWYERS, WHY THAT ONE?

08:29.009 --> 08:33.313
YOUR FRIEND,
KINDRED SPIRIT."

08:33.346 --> 08:35.048
"KINDRED SPIRIT."
I LIKE THAT.

08:35.082 --> 08:36.917
WE SHOULD RUSH A COPY OF THIS
TO THE PAPER

08:36.950 --> 08:38.185
SO THEY CAN GET IT
IN TOMORROW'S EDITION.

08:38.218 --> 08:40.153
MAYBE WE COULD
BRING IT OVER THERE

08:40.187 --> 08:41.521
IN A HORSE AND BUGGY.

08:41.555 --> 08:42.990
IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO BE FUNNY?

08:43.023 --> 08:44.658
LISTEN, PAPERS
HAVE ONLINE EDITIONS.

08:44.692 --> 08:46.493
I'M JUST GONNA POST THIS
AS A COMMENT

08:46.526 --> 08:47.995
TO THE ORIGINAL LETTER,
OKAY?

08:54.034 --> 08:55.803
MAYBE HE'S NOT CHECKING
THE COMMENTS.

08:55.836 --> 08:57.504
MAYBE HE DOESN'T EVEN
OWN A COMPUTER.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.206
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE HE'S LIKE ME.

08:59.239 --> 09:01.675
SOME PEOPLE STILL LIKE THE FEEL
OF A NEWSPAPER IN THEIR HANDS.

09:01.709 --> 09:03.210
WHAT ARE YOU, A LUDDITE?

09:03.243 --> 09:05.345
THE LUDDITES
WERE ONTO SOMETHING.

09:06.814 --> 09:09.349
STUDIES HAVE SHOWN THAT PEOPLE
WHO SPEND TOO MUCH TIME ONLINE

09:09.382 --> 09:11.284
LOSE THE ABILITY TO IDENTIFY
SIMPLE EMOTIONS

09:11.318 --> 09:13.053
EXPRESSED IN PHOTOGRAPHS
OF HUMAN FACES.

09:13.086 --> 09:15.589
I MEAN, COMPUTERS MAY BE THE
GREATEST TECHNOLOGICAL ADVANCE

09:15.623 --> 09:18.058
OF THE LAST 100 YEARS, BUT THIS
WHOLE INTERNET THING IS --

09:18.091 --> 09:20.728
INVALUABLE IN MAKING
INSTANTANEOUS CONTACT

09:20.761 --> 09:22.229
AT CRUCIAL TIMES?

09:22.262 --> 09:24.231
HE ANSWERED?
WHAT DID HE SAY?

09:24.264 --> 09:25.532
"HEY, KINDRED SPIRIT.

09:25.565 --> 09:27.868
"GLAD TO KNOW
I'M NOT ALONE.

09:27.901 --> 09:29.202
"YOU'LL GET
YOUR ANSWER TOMORROW

09:29.236 --> 09:30.604
"WHEN THE NEXT [BLEEP]
GETS HIS MAIL.

09:30.638 --> 09:32.472
"BUT IF YOU'RE AS SMART
AS I THINK YOU ARE,

09:32.505 --> 09:34.041
YOU CAN BE THERE
WHEN IT HAPPENS."

09:34.074 --> 09:35.075
WHAT THE [BLEEP] IS THAT?

09:37.110 --> 09:38.979
IT'S ANOTHER CIPHER.

09:39.012 --> 09:40.714
HE WANTS TO MAKE SURE I'M THE
ONLY ONE THAT GETS THE MESSAGE.

09:40.748 --> 09:42.616
CAN YOU DECIPHER IT?

09:42.650 --> 09:45.152
Codebreaker:
THAT'S A NASTY ONE.

09:49.056 --> 09:52.025
AND IT'S ONLY, WHAT?

09:52.059 --> 09:54.762
SIX HOURS BEFORE
THE MORNING POST COMES 'ROUND.

09:56.797 --> 09:59.767
NOT SURE IF WE CAN CRACK IT
IN TIME.

10:10.443 --> 10:12.880
NO. NO. NO.

10:12.913 --> 10:15.716
IT'S NOT A VIGENÃ¨RE SEQUENCE.

10:15.749 --> 10:17.885
AND IT'S NOT A POLYALPHABETIC
SUBSTITUTION, EITHER.

10:17.918 --> 10:19.552
WHAT THE [BLEEP] IS THAT?

10:19.586 --> 10:21.755
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE
IF IT'S NOT WHAT IT IS?

10:21.789 --> 10:24.658
TRACED THE I.P. ADDRESS THE GUY
USED TO SEND THE REPLY FROM.

10:24.692 --> 10:26.226
CAME UP EMPTY.

10:26.259 --> 10:27.795
CODEBREAKERS AT THE NSA
COME UP WITH ANYTHING?

10:27.828 --> 10:29.462
NOTHING YET.

10:29.496 --> 10:31.398
WELL, THEN
HE BETTER HURRY UP,

10:31.431 --> 10:33.266
BECAUSE THE CHICAGO
POSTAL WORKERS

10:33.300 --> 10:35.402
ARE ABOUT TO HAVE
THEIR MORNING COFFEE!

10:35.435 --> 10:37.938
YEAH, DO YOU NOT THINK I'M
EXCRUCIATINGLY AWARE OF THAT?

10:37.971 --> 10:39.572
I CAN'T --
DON'T -- I CAN'T --

10:39.606 --> 10:42.109
I CAN'T DO THIS WITH EVERYBODY
HOVERING AROUND ME.

10:45.012 --> 10:47.480
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

10:47.514 --> 10:51.418
THOUGHT YOU COULD USE
A LITTLE BIT OF HELP.

10:51.451 --> 10:53.586
YEAH,
YOU'VE BEEN A BIG HELP.

10:53.620 --> 10:55.923
WHAT FUN IS THERE
PLAYING A GAME

10:55.956 --> 10:59.459
IF THE OTHER FELLOW
HASN'T GOT A SPORTING CHANCE?

10:59.492 --> 11:02.662
YOU'RE TALKING IN RIDDLES.
I HAVE ENOUGH OF THOSE.

11:02.696 --> 11:06.099
I'M SIMPLY SAYING IT WOULDN'T
BE CRICKET FOR THIS FELLOW

11:06.133 --> 11:07.667
TO WRITE A CODE

11:07.701 --> 11:10.637
WITHOUT SENDING ALONG AT LEAST
A HINT OF HOW TO CRACK IT.

11:10.670 --> 11:14.641
YOU THINK THE KILLER HID A KEY
WITHIN THE CODE ITSELF.

11:14.674 --> 11:20.147
WELL, IF HE HAD,
HE'D LIKELY OPEN WITH IT...

11:20.180 --> 11:22.215
WOULDN'T HE?

11:24.818 --> 11:28.789
LOOK AT THE NUMBERS,
PIERCE.

11:28.822 --> 11:33.660
LOOK VERY CLOSELY
AT THE NUMBERS.

11:36.897 --> 11:40.868
WHAT IS THE RELATIONSHIP
BETWEEN THE GROUPS OF FIGURES?

11:40.901 --> 11:42.970
[ SIGHS ]

11:43.003 --> 11:46.807
14, 41...

11:46.840 --> 11:50.210
NO. 144. 12.

11:50.243 --> 11:52.379
144 IS THE SQUARE OF 12.

11:52.412 --> 11:54.381
225 IS THE SQUARE
OF 15.

11:54.414 --> 11:56.049
SQUARES AND THEIR ROOTS.

11:56.083 --> 12:00.153
WELL, THAT'S GOT
TO MEAN SOMETHING.

12:00.187 --> 12:02.489
WHAT? WHAT?
S-SQUARE ROOTS.

12:02.522 --> 12:03.723
SQUARES.

12:03.757 --> 12:06.226
N-NOT "ROOT"
LIKE A POTATO.

12:06.259 --> 12:08.528
A ROUTE --
LIKE A HIGHWAY!

12:08.561 --> 12:10.998
IT'S A ROUTE CIPHER.

12:11.031 --> 12:13.166
SQUARES AND THEIR ROOTS --
THE NUMBERS WERE THE TELL.

12:13.200 --> 12:14.501
SQUARES AND THEIR ROOTS.

12:14.534 --> 12:16.069
BUT THE THREE STOOD APART,

12:16.103 --> 12:18.071
MEANING YOU BREAK
EACH STRING OF LETTERS

12:18.105 --> 12:19.773
INTO THREE EQUAL ROWS.

12:19.807 --> 12:21.842
THEN YOU JUST -- YOU JUST HAVE
TO FIGURE OUT THE ROUTE.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.343
IT COULD BE
UP AND DOWN COLUMNS

12:23.376 --> 12:24.477
OR IN A SPIRAL PATTERN --

12:24.511 --> 12:25.712
DANIEL,
THIS IS FANTASTIC,

12:25.745 --> 12:27.514
BUT CAN YOU JUST TELL ME
WHAT IT SAYS?

12:27.547 --> 12:28.515
HERE.

12:28.548 --> 12:29.850
"YOU'D BETTER HURRY.

12:29.883 --> 12:32.853
"FIRST MONUMENT BANK

12:32.886 --> 12:35.923
105 COUCH PLACE."

12:35.956 --> 12:38.425
CALL FIRST MONUMENT BANK,
HAVE THEM CLEAR THE BUILDING

12:38.458 --> 12:41.061
AND WARN THEIR EMPLOYEES
NOT TO OPEN UP ANY MAIL.

12:41.094 --> 12:42.562
I'M GONNA GET
AN AMBULANCE OVER THERE.

12:42.595 --> 12:44.431
TELL THEM TO BRING ATROPINE
AND PRALIDOXIME CHLORIDE

12:44.464 --> 12:47.367
Probert:
WE'RE TOO LATE.RIN.

12:47.400 --> 12:48.802
PRESIDENT OF
FIRST MONUMENT BANK

12:48.836 --> 12:50.237
OPENED A PACKAGE
10 MINUTES AGO.

12:50.270 --> 12:51.371
HE GOT BLASTED WITH SARIN.

12:51.404 --> 12:53.740
HIS NAME'S RUSS ANDERSON.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.408
HE'S ON HIS WAY
TO THE E.R.

13:01.281 --> 13:02.782
IF I'D BEEN
10 MINUTES FASTER,

13:02.816 --> 13:04.684
HE WOULD NOT BE LYING IN THERE
ON LIFE SUPPORT.

13:04.717 --> 13:06.553
DANIEL,
THIS IS NOT YOUR FAULT.

13:06.586 --> 13:08.255
OKAY, YOU DIDN'T
POISON THOSE MEN.

13:08.288 --> 13:10.057
AND WE CAN STILL CATCH THE GUY
WHO DID THIS

13:10.090 --> 13:11.591
BEFORE HE HITS
SOMEONE ELSE.

13:11.624 --> 13:14.828
HAVE YOU GOTTEN AHOLD
OF MR. ANDERSON'S WIFE?

13:14.862 --> 13:18.098
SHE'S ON A PLANE.
SHE'LL BE HERE IN AN HOUR.

13:18.131 --> 13:21.234
I DON'T KNOW
IF HE'LL LAST THAT LONG.

13:21.268 --> 13:22.569
CAN WE TALK TO HIM?

13:22.602 --> 13:23.937
HE'S GONE INTO A COMA.

13:25.172 --> 13:26.706
THAT DOESN'T
NECESSARILY MEAN

13:26.739 --> 13:28.608
WE CAN'T TRY TO ASK HIM
SOME QUESTIONS.

13:35.115 --> 13:38.418
MR. ANDERSON,
MY NAME IS DR. DANIEL PIERCE.

13:38.451 --> 13:40.120
I'M SO SORRY
ABOUT WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU.

13:40.153 --> 13:41.821
YOU'VE BEEN POISONED.

13:41.855 --> 13:43.756
THE DOCTORS HERE ARE DOING
EVERYTHING THEY CAN TO HELP YOU.

13:43.790 --> 13:45.658
YOUR WIFE IS FLYING IN
FROM COLORADO RIGHT NOW.

13:45.692 --> 13:48.161
IN THE MEANTIME,
WE NEED YOUR HELP

13:48.195 --> 13:51.431
CATCHING WHOEVER IT IS
THAT TRIED TO KILL YOU.

13:51.464 --> 13:54.101
I'M GONNA ASK YOU
A SERIES OF QUESTIONS.

13:54.134 --> 13:56.636
WHEN YOU WANT
TO ANSWER "YES,"

13:56.669 --> 13:58.471
THINK ABOUT
THROWING A BASEBALL.

13:58.505 --> 14:03.944
AND FOR "NO," THINK ABOUT
SINGING "HAPPY BIRTHDAY."

14:03.977 --> 14:05.778
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

14:11.051 --> 14:12.785
THAT'S THE CEREBELLUM,
THE REGION OF THE BRAIN

14:12.819 --> 14:14.287
RESPONSIBLE FOR HAND-EYE
COORDINATION.

14:14.321 --> 14:15.788
HE'S THINKING
ABOUT THROWING A BASEBALL.

14:15.822 --> 14:17.624
THIS IS EXTRAORDINARY.

14:17.657 --> 14:19.159
SO HE'S SAYING "YES."

14:19.192 --> 14:21.328
DO YOU KNOW
WHO ATTACKED YOU?

14:22.896 --> 14:24.697
THAT'S THE MEDIAL
PRE-FRONTAL CORTEX.

14:24.731 --> 14:26.533
WHERE WE STORE OUR MEMORIES
OF MUSIC.

14:26.566 --> 14:28.668
HE'S THINKING ABOUT SINGING
"HAPPY BIRTHDAY."

14:28.701 --> 14:30.803
SO HE'S SAYING "NO," HE DOESN'T
KNOW WHO ATTACKED HIM.

14:30.837 --> 14:33.373
DO YOU KNOW A LAWYER
NAMED THOMAS SCANTLIN?

14:33.406 --> 14:35.042
"YES."

14:35.075 --> 14:37.978
DO YOU KNOW MR. SCANTLIN
IN A PERSONAL CAPACITY?

14:38.011 --> 14:40.047
"NO."

14:40.080 --> 14:43.150
IN A PROFESSIONAL
CAPACITY?

14:43.183 --> 14:45.152
"YES."

14:45.185 --> 14:46.486
MR. SCANTLIN
WAS ATTACKED YESTERDAY

14:46.519 --> 14:47.654
THE SAME WAY YOU WERE.

14:47.687 --> 14:50.257
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA WHY?

14:52.059 --> 14:53.826
"YES."

14:53.860 --> 14:57.164
MR. ANDERSON, I'M GONNA ASK YOU
TO SPELL OUT THAT REASON.

14:57.197 --> 14:58.565
I'LL RUN THROUGH THE ALPHABET
LETTER BY LETTER,

14:58.598 --> 15:01.401
AND WHEN I SAY A LETTER
THAT'S CORRECT,

15:01.434 --> 15:03.236
I WANT YOU THINK ABOUT
THROWING THAT BASEBALL.

15:03.270 --> 15:04.437
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

15:05.738 --> 15:08.541
OKAY. HERE WE GO.

15:08.575 --> 15:10.210
"A"...

15:10.243 --> 15:12.479
"D," "E"...

15:13.880 --> 15:16.883
GOT IT.

15:16.916 --> 15:18.718
"DA-FOE." "DAFOE."
I MEAN, IT COULD BE A LAST NAME.

15:18.751 --> 15:22.522
IS THAT RIGHT, MR. ANDERSON?
IS DAFOE SOMEBODY THAT YOU --

15:22.555 --> 15:24.924
[ RAPID BEEPING ]

15:24.958 --> 15:27.194
CODE!

15:31.931 --> 15:34.301
[ ELECTRIC SHOCK ]

15:36.269 --> 15:39.872
[ CHARGING ]

15:39.906 --> 15:41.941
CLEAR!

15:41.975 --> 15:43.910
[ ELECTRIC SHOCK ]

15:43.943 --> 15:45.412
HIS HEART'S STOPPED.

15:45.445 --> 15:49.716
IT'S OVER.

15:49.749 --> 15:51.218
TIME OF DEATH, 10:47 P.M.

16:00.593 --> 16:03.796
MR. DAFOE,
THANK YOU FOR COMING IN.

16:03.830 --> 16:05.465
OF COURSE. YEAH.

16:05.498 --> 16:07.767
I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
RUSS ANDERSON'S DEAD.

16:07.800 --> 16:08.935
HE HAD CHILDREN.

16:08.968 --> 16:10.603
TOM SCANTLIN, TOO.

16:10.637 --> 16:12.705
YOU WERE FRIENDS?

16:12.739 --> 16:14.474
MORE BUSINESS ACQUAINTANCES,
REALLY.

16:14.507 --> 16:16.976
A LUNCH OR TWO A YEAR

16:17.010 --> 16:19.512
AND SHARE A TABLE
AT A CHARITY EVENT,

16:19.546 --> 16:20.880
THAT SORT OF THING.

16:20.913 --> 16:23.316
WE ASKED MR. ANDERSON
IF HE HAD ANY IDEA

16:23.350 --> 16:25.785
WHY HE AND MR. SCANTLIN
WERE TARGETED,

16:25.818 --> 16:28.088
AND THE ONLY THING
HE COULD GIVE US

16:28.121 --> 16:30.023
BEFORE HE DIED
WAS YOUR NAME.

16:30.057 --> 16:31.258
MY NAME?

16:32.325 --> 16:35.995
WAIT, YOU DON'T THINK I HAD
SOMETHING TO DO WITH THE K--

16:36.029 --> 16:39.332
NO. NO. THE KILLER
SEEMS TO HAVE A GRIEVANCE
AGAINST POWERFUL MEN.

16:39.366 --> 16:42.302
YOUR BEING THE C.E.O. OF A
GLOBAL AGRICULTURAL CONGLOMERATE

16:42.335 --> 16:44.137
CERTAINLY PUTS YOU
IN THAT CLUB.

16:44.171 --> 16:46.306
BUT THE KILLER'S
ALSO MADE IT CLEAR

16:46.339 --> 16:49.176
THAT HE HAS THREE MORE VICTIMS
ON HIS LIST.

16:49.209 --> 16:50.243
OH, MY GOD.

16:50.277 --> 16:52.479
WHAT WE NEED
TO DO NOW IS

16:52.512 --> 16:55.482
DETERMINE WHAT POSSIBLY
CONNECTS THE THREE OF YOU

16:55.515 --> 16:58.818
SO WE CAN GET A BETTER IDEA
OF WHO THIS KILLER MIGHT BE.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.420
WELL, CHICAGO'S ULTIMATELY
A SMALL TOWN.

17:00.453 --> 17:02.422
WE'VE DONE SO MUCH BUSINESS
TOGETHER OVER THE YEARS.

17:02.455 --> 17:05.458
DID ANY OF THAT BUSINESS
SCREW SOMEBODY SO BADLY

17:05.492 --> 17:07.827
THAT THEY'D WANT TO SEE ALL
THREE OF YOU FAT CATS DEAD?

17:07.860 --> 17:09.028
I-I'M SORRY,
WHO ARE YOU AGAIN?

17:09.062 --> 17:11.364
SORRY.
THIS IS DR. DANIEL PIERCE.

17:11.398 --> 17:15.068
HE'S A SPECIAL CONSULTANT
HELPING THE FBI WITH THIS CASE.

17:15.102 --> 17:17.170
HE GETS A LITTLE PASSIONATE
SOMETIMES.

17:17.204 --> 17:19.839
WHAT HE'S
TRYING TO ASK IS,

17:19.872 --> 17:23.343
COULD ANY OF YOUR DEALINGS
WITH MR. SCANTLIN OR ANDERSON

17:23.376 --> 17:26.946
HAVE POSSIBLY GIVEN ANYONE
MOTIVE FOR MURDER?

17:26.979 --> 17:30.083
WELL, SCANTLIN'S FIRM
DREW UP THE I.P.O.

17:30.117 --> 17:31.818
THAT WE DID LAST YEAR,

17:31.851 --> 17:35.455
AND A DIVISION OF ANDERSON'S
BANK HANDLED THE OFFERING.

17:35.488 --> 17:39.058
AND WHAT ABOUT THAT
WOULD HAVE SET SOMEONE OFF?

17:39.092 --> 17:41.361
WE HAD TO LAY OFF
13 EXECUTIVES

17:41.394 --> 17:43.863
AND ABOUT 250
LOW-LEVEL EMPLOYEES.

17:43.896 --> 17:46.466
SURE, NOTHING LIKE A LITTLE
CORPORATE DOWNSIZING

17:46.499 --> 17:48.067
TO PUMP UP
THE STOCK PRICE.

17:48.101 --> 17:49.869
GETTING YOUR FISCAL HOUSE
IN ORDER

17:49.902 --> 17:51.571
IS STANDARD BEFORE AN I.P.O.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.973
CAN'T MAKE AN OMELETTE WITHOUT
BREAKING A FEW EGGS, RIGHT?

17:54.006 --> 17:55.308
NO, YOU CAN'T.

17:55.342 --> 17:57.744
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
WE'RE GONNA NEED A LIST

17:57.777 --> 18:03.416
OF THOSE 263 EMPLOYEES,
INCLUDING THE LOW-LEVEL ONES.

18:05.252 --> 18:08.087
ANOTHER NEEDLE
IN ANOTHER HAYSTACK.

18:08.121 --> 18:10.590
MEANWHILE, THE KILLER
COULD BE AT THE POST OFFICE,

18:10.623 --> 18:12.925
DROPPING HIS NEXT DELIVERY
DOWN THE MAIL SLOT.

18:12.959 --> 18:14.894
Daniel: I'LL SEND HIM
ANOTHER FAN LETTER.

18:14.927 --> 18:16.396
MAYBE HE'LL SEND ME
ANOTHER CLUE.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.064
MAYBE THIS TIME I'LL FIGURE
IT OUT FAST ENOUGH.

18:18.097 --> 18:20.066
ALL RIGHT, I'LL LOG BACK
ONTO THE THREAD.

18:20.099 --> 18:23.336
OKAY. UH, NO CODE THIS TIME --
JUST MESSAGE.

18:23.370 --> 18:25.572
UH, "NOW I UNDERSTAND.

18:25.605 --> 18:27.407
"YOU'RE DOWNSIZING
THE [BLEEP]

18:27.440 --> 18:28.941
"THE SAME WAY
THEY DOWNSIZED YOU.

18:28.975 --> 18:31.611
WHO'S NEXT?
YOURS, KINDRED."

18:35.148 --> 18:37.917
OKAY. IT'S SENT.

18:37.950 --> 18:40.420
NOW WE JUST GOT TO HOPE THAT
HE'S MONITORING THE THREAD.

18:40.453 --> 18:43.122
I'M PRETTY SURE
HE'S MONITORING.

18:43.156 --> 18:46.259
FOUR, THREE, TWO...

18:55.302 --> 18:58.037
[ COMPUTER CHIMES ]

18:58.070 --> 18:59.639
"YOU'RE NOT AS SMART
AS I THOUGHT YOU WERE.

18:59.672 --> 19:01.308
"YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND ME
AT ALL.

19:01.341 --> 19:03.710
I'M FINISHED WITH YOU.
GOODBYE."

19:08.581 --> 19:09.816
DANIEL,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:09.849 --> 19:11.284
WHY AREN'T YOU
HELPING KATE?

19:11.318 --> 19:12.819
I-I COULDN'T -- I COULDN'T THINK
IN THAT PLACE.

19:12.852 --> 19:14.187
YOU KNOW,
I-I HAD TO TALK TO YOU.

19:14.221 --> 19:15.755
HOW CAN I HELP?

19:15.788 --> 19:17.490
I THOUGHT I'D MADE A CONNECTION
TO THE KILLER.

19:17.524 --> 19:20.126
YOU KNOW, BUT I-I MUST HAVE
GUESSED WRONG ABOUT HIS MOTIVE,

19:20.159 --> 19:21.961
AND NOW --
NOW HE'S CUT ME OUT.

19:21.994 --> 19:23.196
DID YOU TRY
CONTACTING HIM AGAIN?

19:23.230 --> 19:25.565
NOT UNTIL
I HAVE A BETTER GUESS.

19:25.598 --> 19:30.069
BUT IF HE'S NOT ANGRY ABOUT
BEING DOWNSIZED, WHAT IS IT?

19:30.102 --> 19:31.771
YOU HEAR THOSE SIRENS?

19:31.804 --> 19:34.807
IT SOUNDS LIKE
IT'S RIGHT NEXT DOOR.

19:37.210 --> 19:40.012
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

19:41.548 --> 19:44.684
OH, SORRY. SORRY.

19:44.717 --> 19:46.719
I WORK -- I WORK HERE.

19:49.021 --> 19:50.156
KATE?

19:50.189 --> 19:51.491
WHAT THE [BLEEP]
GOING ON?

19:51.524 --> 19:52.859
LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU GET IT.

19:52.892 --> 19:54.827
OKAY, DANIEL, LISTEN.
IT WAS SARIN AGAIN.

19:54.861 --> 19:56.496
IT WAS PACKED IN A CANISTER
LIKE THE OTHERS

19:56.529 --> 19:58.831
WITH A CHARGE TO RELEASE THE GAS
WHEN THE PACKAGE WAS OPENED.

19:58.865 --> 20:00.500
NOBODY.NED IT?

20:00.533 --> 20:02.502
LOOKS LIKE IT WAS DROPPED
AND WENT OFF ACCIDENTALLY.

20:02.535 --> 20:04.837
THE VICTIM
WAS KELLY OWENS.

20:04.871 --> 20:07.173
SHE WAS WORKING PART-TIME
IN THE FACULTY MAIL ROOM.

20:07.206 --> 20:08.341
OH, THAT POOR GIRL.

20:08.375 --> 20:09.709
AND HER PARENTS.

20:09.742 --> 20:11.110
WELL, OBVIOUSLY
SHE WASN'T THE TARGET.

20:11.143 --> 20:12.679
WHO WAS THE PACKAGE
ADDRESSED TO?

20:12.712 --> 20:14.681
MAILING LABEL WAS INCINERATED
IN THE EXPLOSION.

20:14.714 --> 20:15.848
WE DON'T KNOW.

20:15.882 --> 20:17.850
ACTUALLY,
I'M PRETTY SURE WE DO.

20:17.884 --> 20:20.219
OUR MAD SCIENTIST HERE
MADE THE PAPER.

20:20.253 --> 20:22.689
WHAT?

20:22.722 --> 20:25.892
"ANONYMOUS SOURCES REPORT
THAT DR. DANIEL PIERCE OF CLMU

20:25.925 --> 20:27.394
"HAS BEEN HELPING THE FBI

20:27.427 --> 20:29.729
DECIPHER THE KILLER'S
CODED MESSAGES."

20:29.762 --> 20:31.731
HE FOUND OUT HIS KINDRED
SPIRIT'S TALKING TO THE COPS.

20:31.764 --> 20:33.466
"ANONYMOUS SOURCES."

20:33.500 --> 20:35.468
WHAT, HAVE YOU BEEN BLABBING
TO THWHO, ME?

20:35.502 --> 20:37.870
THERE'S DOZENS OF AGENTS
WORKING ON THIS CASE.

20:37.904 --> 20:39.706
AND IF YOU THINK THAT I WOULD
JEOPARDIZE MY CAREER

20:39.739 --> 20:41.674
TO GET YOUR NAME IN THE PAPER,
YOU'RE CRAZIER THAN I THOUGHT.

20:41.708 --> 20:42.975
LISTEN, THERE WILL BE AN
INVESTIGATION INTO THE LEAK.

20:43.009 --> 20:46.012
WHAT MATTERS NOW
IS THAT YOU'RE IN DANGER.

20:46.045 --> 20:47.747
NO, NO, I DON'T BUY IT.
I DON'T BUY IT.

20:47.780 --> 20:50.049
THIS GUY'S A METHODICAL KILLER
WITH AN URGENT AGENDA.

20:50.082 --> 20:51.884
HE'S NOT GONNA WASTE TIME
ON SOME DETOUR

20:51.918 --> 20:54.020
JUST 'CAUSE HE FINDS OUT
I'M N HIS BEST FRIEND.

20:54.053 --> 20:55.722
WE NEED TO ERR
ON THE SIDE OF CAUTION.

20:55.755 --> 20:57.023
I'M TAKING YOU HOME AND HAVING
YOU GUARDED, ALL RIGHT?

20:57.056 --> 20:58.691
COME ON.

20:58.725 --> 21:00.192
NO, NO,
I DON'T WANT SOME STRANGER

21:00.226 --> 21:01.761
LURKING AROUND MY HOUSE.

21:01.794 --> 21:04.297
OKAY, FINE.

21:04.331 --> 21:05.932
IT'LL HAVE TO BE SOMEONE
WHO YOU ALREADY KNOW.

21:16.443 --> 21:17.744
YOU GOT CABLE?

21:17.777 --> 21:20.246
[ STAMMERS, SCOFFS ]

21:26.453 --> 21:30.022
THAT PACKAGE WASN'T MEANT
FOR ME.

21:30.056 --> 21:31.524
DANIEL, MAYBE YOU DON'T
WANT TO ACCEPT IT

21:31.558 --> 21:33.192
BECAUSE THEN YOU'D
HAVE TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY

21:33.225 --> 21:35.695
FOR WHAT HAPPENED
TO THAT POOR GIRL.

21:35.728 --> 21:37.964
THAT'S NOT WHAT I'M SAYING.
I-I AM RESPONSIBLE.

21:37.997 --> 21:41.568
I MEAN, IF I'D CAUGHT THE KILLER
ASORRY TO INTERRUPT.-

21:41.601 --> 21:43.836
DO YOU MIND?

21:43.870 --> 21:46.539
OH, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE TALKING TO SOMEONE.

21:46.573 --> 21:47.840
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

21:47.874 --> 21:49.542
MUSTARD.

21:49.576 --> 21:50.843
WHAT?

21:50.877 --> 21:53.279
YOU KNOW, GREY POUPON,
YELLOW?

21:53.312 --> 21:54.714
I'M MAKING A SANDWICH.

21:54.747 --> 21:57.484
LEWICKI!

22:00.086 --> 22:02.221
YES.

22:02.254 --> 22:05.592
WOULD YOU GET THE GOOD AGENT
SOME MUSTARD?

22:05.625 --> 22:07.760
UH, I'M ON STRIKE,
REMEMBER?

22:07.794 --> 22:10.363
LEWICKI,
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS.

22:10.397 --> 22:11.664
THEN I SUGGEST
YOU SAY "PLEASE."

22:11.698 --> 22:15.001
AND I SUGGEST
YOU GET THE [BLEEP] MUSTARD.

22:15.034 --> 22:16.669
FINE.

22:16.703 --> 22:18.337
BUT NOT BECAUSE
YOU ORDERED ME TO --

22:18.371 --> 22:20.507
BECAUSE
I'M A NICE PERSON.

22:20.540 --> 22:21.874
RIGHT THIS WAY.

22:22.842 --> 22:26.312
IF THE PACKAGE WASN'T FOR YOU,
WHO WAS IT FOR?

22:26.345 --> 22:27.647
I DON'T NOW.

22:27.680 --> 22:29.616
SOMEONE ON CAMPUS

22:29.649 --> 22:32.785
WHO IS SOMEHOW CONNECTED TO
ANDERSON, SCANTLIN, AND DAFOE.

22:32.819 --> 22:34.887
WELL, LET'S TAKE THEM
ONE AT A TIME.

22:34.921 --> 22:36.489
WHAT FIELD IS DAFOE IN?

22:36.523 --> 22:39.826
HE'S A C.E.O. --

22:39.859 --> 22:42.094
WHERE THE [BLEEP]
MY FACULTY DIRECTORY?

22:42.128 --> 22:44.431
IN HERE,

22:46.065 --> 22:48.200
UNDER THE GONG.

22:48.234 --> 22:49.702
[ GONG CLANKS ]

22:49.736 --> 22:53.139
COLLEGE OF AGRICULTURE.

22:55.642 --> 22:59.278
ARTHUR WEI --
HOLDS THE DISTINGUISHED

22:59.311 --> 23:01.614
FREDERICK JAMES DAFOE
PROFESSORSHIP

23:01.648 --> 23:04.283
OF GENETIC ENGINEERING.

23:04.316 --> 23:05.452
PROBERT!

23:10.523 --> 23:12.124
CAN I HELP YOU?

23:12.158 --> 23:14.160
I'M DR. DANIEL PIERCE,
DEPARTMENT OF NEUROSCIENCE.

23:14.193 --> 23:15.828
THIS IS AGENT PROBERT
OF THE FBI.

23:15.862 --> 23:16.929
FBI?
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

23:16.963 --> 23:19.298
THIS CONVERSATION
IS PRIVATE.

23:19.331 --> 23:20.933
I ASSUME YOU HEARD
ABOUT KELLY OWENS,

23:20.967 --> 23:22.502
THE GIRL WHO DIED
ON CAMPUS TODAY?

23:22.535 --> 23:23.503
YEAH, IT'S TERRIBLE.

23:23.536 --> 23:25.037
IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN YOU.

23:25.071 --> 23:26.238
EXCUSE ME?

23:26.272 --> 23:28.307
YOU WERE THE TARGET.

23:28.340 --> 23:30.142
WHAT'S YOUR CONNECTION
TO FREDERICK DAFOE,

23:30.176 --> 23:31.878
APART FROM THE FACT THAT YOU
HOLD A CHAIR GENEROUSLY ENDOWED

23:31.911 --> 23:32.945
BY HIS FOUNDATION?

23:32.979 --> 23:34.547
WHAT THE [BLEEP] IS THIS?

23:34.581 --> 23:35.915
LOOK,
EITHER YOU TALK TO ME,

23:35.948 --> 23:37.149
OR I GET THAT GUY OUT THERE

23:37.183 --> 23:38.718
TO PHONE HIS BUDDIES
AT THE BUREAU,

23:38.751 --> 23:41.153
AND THEN IT'S THE HANDCUFFS,
THE ALL-NIGHT INTERROGATION,

23:41.187 --> 23:42.655
SWEATING IN A DAMP CELL

23:42.689 --> 23:44.223
UNTIL YOU FINALLY BREAK
AND SPILL IT ANYWAY.

23:44.256 --> 23:46.526
ALL IN ALL, I'D SAY
YOUR BEST BET IS TALKING TO ME.

23:46.559 --> 23:48.327
NOW, WHAT DID YOU DO
FOR FREDERICK DAFOE

23:48.360 --> 23:49.962
THAT GOT YOU
THE ENDOWED CHAIR?

23:52.799 --> 23:55.367
I'M AN AGRICULTURAL
GENETICIST.

23:55.401 --> 23:58.971
I CREATED A NEW STRAIN OF CORN
FOR HIS COMPANY.

23:59.005 --> 24:00.507
WHY WOULD SOMEONE
TRY TO KILL YOU FOR THAT?

24:07.747 --> 24:11.050
LOOK, WHILE I WAS WORKING
ON THE GENE,

24:11.083 --> 24:13.720
I REALIZED THERE WAS
A POSSIBILITY

24:13.753 --> 24:16.422
OF A TROUBLING
COLLATERAL EFFECT.

24:16.455 --> 24:18.591
WHAT "COLLATERAL EFFECT"?

24:18.625 --> 24:21.260
MY STRAIN OF CORN WAS
GENETICALLY DOMINANT.

24:21.293 --> 24:23.963
IF THE SEED BLEW
INTO THE NEIGHBORING FARM,

24:23.996 --> 24:26.132
IT WOULD WIPE OUT
THE NATIVE CORN

24:26.165 --> 24:28.601
AND TAKE OVER
THE OTHER FARMER'S FIELD.

24:28.635 --> 24:31.771
I WAS TRYING
TO RE-ENGINEER THE SEED

24:31.804 --> 24:34.774
SO IT COULD ACHIEVE HARMONY
WITH THE OTHER STRAINS,

24:34.807 --> 24:38.210
BUT DAFOE
ORDERED ME NOT TO.

24:38.244 --> 24:39.311
WHY?

24:39.345 --> 24:41.213
AT THE TIME,
I DIDN'T KNOW IT,

24:41.247 --> 24:44.016
BUT ONCE THE GENE SPREAD
TO THE NEIGHBORING FARMS,

24:44.050 --> 24:47.153
DAFOE STARTED SUING THE FARMERS
FOR SELLING HIS CORN --

24:47.186 --> 24:48.888
MY CORN --
TO THE CONSUMER.

24:48.921 --> 24:50.590
[ Scoffing ]
ON WHAT GROUNDS?

24:50.623 --> 24:52.525
COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT.

24:52.559 --> 24:55.261
HE HELD THE PATENT
ON THE GENE.

24:55.294 --> 24:56.929
HE SUED THEM FOR SELLING
A STRAIN OF CORN

24:56.963 --> 24:57.764
THAT BLEW IN ON THE WIND?

24:57.797 --> 24:59.165
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

24:59.198 --> 25:02.234
LOOK, THEY DIDN'T REALIZE
THEY WERE GROWING IT.

25:02.268 --> 25:04.403
A LOT OF THEM
WENT INTO FORECLOSURE.

25:04.436 --> 25:06.105
OH. OF COURSE.
LET ME GUESS --

25:06.138 --> 25:08.240
DAFOE STARTED BUYING UP
THEIR FARMS ON THE CHEAP.

25:08.274 --> 25:09.542
I WENT TO DAFOE.

25:09.576 --> 25:11.343
I TOLD HIM
IF HE DOESN'T DROP THE SUITS,

25:11.377 --> 25:13.179
I WOULD INFORM
THE DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE

25:13.212 --> 25:14.781
THAT HE'D PLANNED
THE WHOLE THING.

25:14.814 --> 25:17.283
RIGHT, AND THEN HE OFFERED YOU
THE ENDOWED CHAIR

25:17.316 --> 25:19.552
AND MAYBE A LITTLE GRANT MONEY
AS A KICKER.

25:19.586 --> 25:21.020
YOU'RE A SCIENTIST.

25:21.053 --> 25:23.956
YOU KNOW HOW HARD IT IS
TO GET FUNDING --

25:23.990 --> 25:25.424
SPARE ME THAT CRAP.

25:25.457 --> 25:27.326
YOU TOOK YOUR 30 PIECES
OF SILVER,

25:27.359 --> 25:28.761
AND THOSE FARMERS
LOST EVERYTHING.

25:28.795 --> 25:30.563
NO, YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

25:30.597 --> 25:33.766
NO, I THINK I UNDERSTAND
JUST FINE...PROFESSOR.

25:33.800 --> 25:35.768
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

25:35.802 --> 25:41.440
Kate: KEVIN LANG, CAL BOWDEN,
RAY DONALDSON --

25:41.473 --> 25:43.943
ANY OF THESE NAMES MEAN ANYTHING
TO YOU, MR. DAFOE?

25:43.976 --> 25:46.012
UH, NO,
I'VE NEVER HEARD OF THEM.

25:46.045 --> 25:47.847
OF COURSE NOT.
YOU GOT LAWYERS FOR THAT.

25:47.880 --> 25:50.850
LANG, BOWDEN, AND DONALDSON
WERE THREE OF THE FARMERS

25:50.883 --> 25:53.352
WHOSE LIVES YOU RUINED
WHEN YOU SUED THEM

25:53.385 --> 25:57.189
FOR COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT
FOR UNKNOWINGLY TAKING CORN

25:57.223 --> 25:59.291
CONTAINING THE DAFOE GENE
TO MARKET.

25:59.325 --> 26:02.595
THAT GENE WAS PATENTED.

26:02.629 --> 26:04.697
YEAH, AND DESIGNED TO OBLITERATE
EVERY CORNSTALK IN ITS PATH.

26:04.731 --> 26:06.699
Kate: SCANTLIN HANDLED
THE LAWSUITS,

26:06.733 --> 26:09.101
AND THEN ANDERSON FAST-TRACKED
THE FARMS TO FORECLOSURE,

26:09.135 --> 26:10.870
SO YOU COULD SNAP UP
THOSE PROPERTIES

26:10.903 --> 26:12.171
FOR PENNIES
ON THE DOLLAR.

26:12.204 --> 26:13.973
YES, THAT'S CALLED
GOOD BUSINESS.

26:14.006 --> 26:17.309
U.S. ATTORNEY'S GONNA CALL IT
CONSPIRACY TO COMMIT FRAUD.

26:17.343 --> 26:18.611
ALL RIGHT,
LISTEN, SWEETIE,

26:18.645 --> 26:20.546
I'M NOT GONNA SAY
ANOTHER WORD TO YOU

26:20.579 --> 26:22.982
WITHOUT A LAWTHAT'S FINE.

26:23.015 --> 26:26.819
BUT IN THE MEANTIME,
THE KILLER IS STILL OUT THERE.

26:26.853 --> 26:29.588
IT'S A PRETTY GOOD BET
THAT YOU ARE ON HIS LIST.

26:29.622 --> 26:31.824
SO I SUGGEST YOU TELL US

26:31.858 --> 26:34.627
WHICH OF THE FARMERS YOU RUINED
MIGHT BE DOING THIS.

26:34.661 --> 26:40.332
OKAY, THERE WAS AN INCIDENT
AT THE SHAREHOLDERS MEETING.

26:40.366 --> 26:43.335
A VERY ANGRY MAN
STORMED INTO THE ROOM,

26:43.369 --> 26:46.739
YELLING THREATS AND OBSCENITIES,
AND HE HAD TO BE ESCORTED OUT.

26:46.773 --> 26:47.907
I NEED A NAME.

26:47.940 --> 26:49.208
I DON'T KNOW.

26:49.241 --> 26:51.110
MAYBE MY SECURITY PEOPLE
MIGHT HAVE IT.

26:51.143 --> 26:54.080
LOOK, ARE YOU GOING TO
BE ABLE TO KEEP ME SAFE?

26:54.113 --> 26:57.516
OH, YEAH.
U.S. MARSHALS WILL PROTECT YOU.

26:57.549 --> 26:59.719
AFTER ALL, WE WOULDN'T WANT
ANYTHING HAPPENING TO YOU

26:59.752 --> 27:02.188
BEFORE YOU CAN START SERVING
YOUR SENTENCE.

27:08.494 --> 27:11.397
GOT THE NAME OF THE FARMER THAT
STORMED THE SHAREHOLDER MEETING

27:11.430 --> 27:14.566
AND THREATENED DAFOE --
PAUL LEVASSEUR.

27:14.600 --> 27:16.068
GREAT.
LET'S GO PICK HIM UP.

27:16.102 --> 27:18.671
HE'S SERVING 8 TO 10
IN STATEVILLE PRISON.

27:18.705 --> 27:20.807
BEEN THERE THREE MONTHS.

27:22.675 --> 27:24.076
NOT OUR GUY.

27:24.110 --> 27:26.746
BUT MAYBE HE CAN
TELL US WHO IS.

27:26.779 --> 27:29.048
HOW DO YOU FIGURE THAT?

27:29.081 --> 27:32.051
WHY DID THE KILLER PUT
HIS MESSAGE IN A NEWSPAPER?

27:32.084 --> 27:33.920
MAYBE BECAUSE HE WAS SENDING IT
TO SOMEBODY

27:33.953 --> 27:36.255
WHOSE LETTERS GET OPENED
AND READ

27:36.288 --> 27:37.556
BEFORE THEY'RE DELIVERED.

27:37.589 --> 27:39.191
SOMEONE IN PRISON.

27:41.027 --> 27:46.665
MY GREAT-GREAT-GRANDFATHER
HOMESTEADED THAT LAND.

27:46.699 --> 27:50.302
MY FAMILY...
FARMED IT FOR 100 YEARS.

27:50.336 --> 27:54.673
AFTER THE LAWSUIT, I TRIED
OTHER THINGS TO GET BY.

27:54.707 --> 27:57.009
SOLD TRACTORS.

27:57.043 --> 28:01.013
DUG DITCHES FOR THE COUNTY.

28:01.047 --> 28:02.681
NOTHING STUCK.

28:02.715 --> 28:04.583
SO YOU ROBBED A BANK.

28:04.616 --> 28:07.019
JUST TRYING TO KEEP MY FAMILY
ABOVE WATER.

28:07.053 --> 28:10.857
LOSING THE FARM,
SEEING ME BEHIND BARS...

28:10.890 --> 28:13.860
BROKE MY WIFE'S HEART.

28:13.893 --> 28:16.528
SHE HUNG HERSELF
NINE WEEKS AGO.

28:16.562 --> 28:19.398
I'M SO SORRY.

28:20.900 --> 28:22.935
LISTEN, MR. LEVASSEUR,

28:22.969 --> 28:26.305
WE'RE HERE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR SON, EDDIE.

28:26.338 --> 28:28.007
Daniel: THE CODED MESSAGE
IN THE NEWSPAPER --

28:28.040 --> 28:30.743
HE PUT THAT THERE FOR YOU,
DIDN'T HE?

28:32.678 --> 28:35.147
"FRONT-PAGE NEWS."

28:35.181 --> 28:38.050
JUST LIKE HE SAID.

28:38.084 --> 28:41.821
I TRIED TO CALL HIM
AFTER I READ ABOUT SCANTLIN,

28:41.854 --> 28:43.823
BUT HIS PHONE WAS TURNED OFF.

28:43.856 --> 28:45.892
YOU COULD HAVE CALLED
THE POLICE.

28:45.925 --> 28:49.561
[ Crying ]
I KNOW I SHOULD HAVE, BUT...

28:49.595 --> 28:51.397
HE WAS YOUR BOY.

28:51.430 --> 28:52.865
YOU COULDN'T BEAR
TO TURN HIM IN.

28:55.401 --> 28:58.704
AFTER --
AFTER THIS ALL WENT DOWN,

28:58.737 --> 29:00.572
SOMETHING IN HIM BROKE.

29:00.606 --> 29:05.077
BUT I SWEAR TO YOU,
HE'S A GOOD BOY.

29:05.111 --> 29:06.512
A BRILLIANT BOY.

29:06.545 --> 29:08.848
FINISHED COLLEGE
IN THREE YEARS.

29:08.881 --> 29:11.784
COULDN'T WAIT TO GET STARTED IN
ON HIS PhD.

29:11.818 --> 29:14.053
BUT HE HAD TO DROP OUT
AFTER YOU LOST THE FARM.

29:14.086 --> 29:15.587
I COULDN'T SEND HIM A DIME.

29:15.621 --> 29:19.091
HE'S BEEN TEACHING
HIGH-SCHOOL MATH IN HARVEY.

29:19.125 --> 29:22.594
ACTUALLY, HE HASN'T BEEN THERE
IN OVER A MONTH.

29:22.628 --> 29:25.264
HE HASN'T BEEN BACK
TO HIS APARTMENT, EITHER.

29:25.297 --> 29:27.934
WE NEED TO FIND HIM
BEFORE SOMEONE ELSE DIES.

29:27.967 --> 29:31.303
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE HE IS?

29:33.405 --> 29:36.742
THERE'S A -- THERE'S A PLACE
HE USED TO LIKE TO GO TO THINK.

29:38.344 --> 29:40.146
ON THE BACK ACREAGE
OF OUR OLD FARM.

29:50.556 --> 29:52.324
LOOK AT THIS.
HE KNEW WE WERE COMING.

29:55.494 --> 29:58.397
"HEY, KINDRED,
MY LIFE'S AN OPEN BOOK.

29:58.430 --> 30:00.732
"WHEN YOU CRACK THIS ONE,
YOU'LL KNOW EVERYTHING.

30:00.766 --> 30:01.901
"BUT SEARCH YOUR MIND.

30:01.934 --> 30:03.335
DO YOU REALLY
WANT TO STOP ME?"

30:03.369 --> 30:04.971
WHAT IS IT WITH THIS GUY?

30:05.004 --> 30:07.273
FIRST HE BLOWS YOU OFF,
THEN HE LEAVES YOU ANOTHER CLUE?

30:07.306 --> 30:08.707
HE WANTS TO AVENGE
THE INJUSTICE

30:08.740 --> 30:10.442
DONE TO HIS FATHER
AND THE OTHER FARMERS,

30:10.476 --> 30:12.644
BUT HE DID NOT MEAN TO KILL
AN INNOCENT COLLEGE STUDENT,

30:12.678 --> 30:15.114
SO MAYBE HE'S FEELING GUILTY
OR CONFLICTED.

30:15.147 --> 30:17.249
SOME PART OF HIM
WANTS TO GET CAUGHT.

30:17.283 --> 30:18.918
LET'S GIVE HIM
WHAT HE WANTS.

30:18.951 --> 30:20.252
"MY LIFE'S AN OPEN BOOK."

30:20.286 --> 30:23.289
"OPEN BOOK."
IT'S A BOOK CIPHER.

30:23.322 --> 30:25.157
LOOK, THE NUMBERS
ARE IN GROUPS OF THREE.

30:25.191 --> 30:26.859
THE FIRST ONE CORRESPONDS
TO A PAGE NUMBER

30:26.893 --> 30:28.160
IN A PARTICULAR BOOK,

30:28.194 --> 30:29.795
THE SECOND ONE --
SECOND NUMBER TO --

30:29.828 --> 30:31.297
TO A LINE ON THAT PAGE,

30:31.330 --> 30:32.932
AND THE THIRD NUMBER TO A WORD
IN THAT LINE.

30:32.965 --> 30:34.266
YOU FIND THE WORDS,
YOU PUT THEM TOGETHER,

30:34.300 --> 30:35.301
YOU GET YOUR MESSAGE.

30:35.334 --> 30:37.970
IT COULD --

30:38.004 --> 30:41.273
IT COULD BE ANY BOOK
IN THE WORLD.

30:41.307 --> 30:43.209
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING,
OLD BOY.

30:45.978 --> 30:48.447
HE'S TELLING YOU EVERYTHING
YOU NEED TO KNOW.

30:48.480 --> 30:49.882
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

30:49.916 --> 30:52.885
I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

30:55.221 --> 30:58.657
"SEARCH YOUR MIND,"
PIERCE.

30:58.690 --> 31:01.894
I AM. I AM.

31:01.928 --> 31:03.362
It's not helping!

31:03.395 --> 31:06.132
DANIEL, YOU ALL RIGHT?

31:06.165 --> 31:07.533
YEAH. DON'T --
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

31:07.566 --> 31:11.303
OKAY? I'M F-FINE.
JUST DON'T WORRY ABOUT...

31:11.337 --> 31:13.805
ME.

31:13.839 --> 31:17.309
YOU NEED TO TAKE ME HOME.

31:17.343 --> 31:18.510
Daniel:
THIS IS OUR KEY.

31:18.544 --> 31:19.912
"THE MIND:
KNOWING THE UNKNOWABLE".

31:19.946 --> 31:21.880
BY DR. DANIEL PIERCE.
I LOVE THIS BOOK.

31:21.914 --> 31:23.215
BUT WHAT DO YOU --

31:23.249 --> 31:24.883
HE'S NOT SAYING
"SEARCH YOUR MIND."

31:24.917 --> 31:26.552
HE'S SAYING
"SEARCH YOUR MIND."

31:26.585 --> 31:28.554
HE MEANS THE TITLE
OF YYEAH.OOK.

31:29.956 --> 31:34.893
GO TO PAGE...312.

31:34.927 --> 31:37.229
SECOND LINE, THIRD WORD.

31:37.263 --> 31:39.698
"TODAY."

31:42.834 --> 31:44.070
PAGE 57.

31:44.103 --> 31:47.773
17th LINE, 12th WORD.

31:58.184 --> 32:00.819
14th LINE, 9th WORD.

32:00.852 --> 32:02.754
"FAMILY."

32:05.124 --> 32:06.925
"TODAY I DESTROY
THE VILLAIN

32:06.959 --> 32:10.029
THE SAME WAY THE VILLAIN
DESTROYED MY FAMILY."

32:10.062 --> 32:13.199
"DESTROY THE VILLAIN."
WHO'S HE TALKING ABOUT?

32:13.232 --> 32:14.833
IT'S GOT TO BE DAFOE.

32:14.866 --> 32:16.668
I MEAN, HE'S THE MAIN VILLAIN
IN THIS WHOLE SORDID STORY.

32:16.702 --> 32:18.170
DAFOE IS IN
PROTECTIVE CUSTODY.

32:18.204 --> 32:20.472
HOW'S THE KILLER
GONNA DESTROY HIM THERE?

32:20.506 --> 32:22.574
THERE ARE A MILLION WAYS
TO DESTROY SOMEONE

32:22.608 --> 32:24.176
WHOSE ONLY PRIORITY
IS PROFITS.

32:24.210 --> 32:26.945
I MEAN, YOU COULD TAKE OUT
THEIR PROCESSING PLANTS,

32:26.979 --> 32:30.549
OR THEIR WAREHOUSES
OR THEIR GRAIN ELEVATORS.

32:30.582 --> 32:31.750
YEAH,
IT'S A HUGE COMPANY.

32:31.783 --> 32:33.052
WE DON'T HAVE THE MANPOWER

32:33.085 --> 32:34.553
TO PROTECT EVERY ONE
OF HIS FACILITIES.

32:34.586 --> 32:36.155
BUT WE CAN TRY.
JUST GET THE BOSS ON THE PHONE.

32:38.390 --> 32:41.160
Codebreaker:
A WORD WITH YOU, OLD CHAP?

32:45.831 --> 32:47.466
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

32:47.499 --> 32:50.469
"TODAY
I DESTROY THE VILLAIN

32:50.502 --> 32:53.139
THE SAME WAY THE VILLAIN
DESTROYED MY FAMILY."

32:53.172 --> 32:54.306
YEAH. SO?

32:54.340 --> 32:55.641
PERHAPS
THERE'S ANOTHER CODE

32:55.674 --> 32:57.243
BURIED IN
THE MESSAGE ITSELF.

32:57.276 --> 33:00.779
Natalie: DANIEL, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO LISTEN TO HIM.

33:01.847 --> 33:03.482
EACH LETTER
REPRESENTS A NUMBER.

33:03.515 --> 33:05.984
YOU DON'T NEED HIS HELP.

33:06.018 --> 33:08.087
PERHAPS IT'S AN ADDRESS.

33:08.120 --> 33:09.655
YOU'VE CRACKED THE CIPHERS.

33:09.688 --> 33:11.323
NOW IT'S ABOUT
CRACKING EDDIE.

33:11.357 --> 33:14.026
[ STAMMERS ]
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

33:14.060 --> 33:16.428
WHAT DID DAFOE DO
THAT REALLY HURT HIM?

33:16.462 --> 33:18.264
DID HE TAKE AWAY HIS FARM,

33:18.297 --> 33:23.001
HIS LIVELIHOOD, OR SOMETHING
MORE IMPORTANT TO HIM?

33:29.041 --> 33:30.709
I LOVE YOU, NATALIE VINCENT.

33:32.144 --> 33:35.013
I DID IT.
I-I SOLVED THE RIDDLE.

33:35.047 --> 33:37.015
SO DO WE.AT EDDIE'S DOING.

33:37.049 --> 33:38.984
OUR AGENTS FOUND A TRUCK BOMB
FULL OF FERTILIZER

33:39.017 --> 33:41.053
JUST OUTSIDE
DAFOE HEADQUARTERS.

33:41.087 --> 33:43.455
WHAT? NO. NO, NO, NO.
THAT'S A DECOY.

33:43.489 --> 33:45.691
REMEMBER THE ORIGINAL MESSAGE --
"ONE DOWN, FOUR TO GO."

33:45.724 --> 33:47.359
THAT MAKES FIVE VICTIMS.

33:47.393 --> 33:50.462
NOW EDDIE'S TELLING US,
"TODAY I DESTROY THE VILLAIN

33:50.496 --> 33:52.631
THE SAME WAY THE VILLAIN
DESTROYED MY FAMILY."

33:52.664 --> 33:55.534
H-HIS FATHER'S IN PRISON,
HIS MOTHER TOOK HER OWN LIFE,

33:55.567 --> 33:57.203
ALL BECAUSE OF DAFOE.

33:57.236 --> 33:59.538
THREE OF THE VICTIMS ARE DEAD.
WHO ARE THE LAST TWO?

33:59.571 --> 34:02.341
DAFOE'S PARENTS.

34:07.079 --> 34:08.647
HE'S IN THERE
WITH THE DAFOES.

34:08.680 --> 34:11.317
QUESTION IS,
WHAT'S HE WAITING FOR?

34:11.350 --> 34:13.419
HE'S WAITING
TO TALK TO ME.

34:14.686 --> 34:17.289
WANT TO GIVE THIS A TRY?

34:17.323 --> 34:18.557
NO, IT'S GOT TO BE
FACE-TO-FACE.

34:18.590 --> 34:19.958
DANIEL,
YOU'RE NOT GOING IN THERE.

34:19.991 --> 34:21.193
HE TOLD ME
HOW TO FIND HIM.

34:21.227 --> 34:22.761
HE MUST HAVE SOMETHING
TO SAY TO ME.

34:23.629 --> 34:27.166
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
I'M GOING IN WITH YOU.

34:27.199 --> 34:28.334
AND YOU'RE WEARING A WIRE

34:28.367 --> 34:29.901
SO SWAT CAN HEAR
WHAT'S GOING ON.

34:29.935 --> 34:31.837
LOOK, IF YOU CAN GET HIM
IN FRONT OF A WINDOW,

34:31.870 --> 34:33.405
ONE OF MY SNIPERS
CAN TAKE HIM OUT.

34:33.439 --> 34:35.441
[ SIGHS ]

34:47.586 --> 34:51.056
UH, EDDIE,
I'M DR. DANIEL PIERCE.

34:51.089 --> 34:52.458
MAY I COME IN?

34:56.228 --> 34:57.429
JUST HIM.

34:57.463 --> 34:59.365
AND IF YOU OR ANYONE ELSE

34:59.398 --> 35:00.899
SO MUCH AS RATTLES
THIS DOORKNOB,

35:00.932 --> 35:01.733
I PRESS THIS BUTTON,
AND WE ALL GO UP TOGETHER.

35:01.767 --> 35:04.703
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

35:04.736 --> 35:05.837
DANIEL.

35:05.871 --> 35:09.241
I-I CAN DO IT.

35:28.927 --> 35:31.563
THERE'S A WAY
OUT OF THIS, EDDIE.

35:31.597 --> 35:33.399
THERE'S NO OTHER WAY
OUT FOR ME.

35:33.432 --> 35:36.268
IF YOU BELIEVE THAT,

35:36.302 --> 35:39.104
THEN WHY DID YOU TELL ME
WHERE TO FIND YOU?

35:39.137 --> 35:40.939
I MEAN,
THE PUZZLES WERE CLEVER,

35:40.972 --> 35:43.775
BUT YOU KNEW
I'D BE ABLE TO SOLVE THEM.

35:43.809 --> 35:45.177
YEAH.
I WANTED YOU HERE...

35:45.211 --> 35:47.413
BECAUSE YOU SAID
